$ PowerShell: the automatic variable $PsVersionTable

`$psVersionTable` is an → Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/automatic[automatic] variable (a hash table) that reveals some information about the PowerShwell that runs the current → Windows/PowerShell/session[session].

{ Determine PowerShell version

  Print → Windows/PowerShell[PowerShell's] version with `$PSversionTable` …
code { #psVersion-powerShell-version
PS C:\> ($psVersionTable).psVersion

Major  Minor  Build  Revision
-----  -----  -----  --------
5      1      17763  134
code }

  … or alternatively use → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/host/get/version[`get-host`]:
code {
PS C:\> (get-host).version

Major  Minor  Build  Revision
-----  -----  -----  --------
5      1      17763  134
code }

}

sa:
  Other → Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/automatic[automatic variables]
